Hey, Ralphie.

02:19.783 --> 02:21.449
Hello, ladies.

02:21.451 --> 02:24.986
We need you to sign off on
the Sadie Hawkins Dance theme.

02:24.988 --> 02:27.021
We're doing '80s again, okay?

02:27.023 --> 02:29.257
Leg-warmers and side ponies, y'all.

02:29.726 --> 02:31.426
Well, I don't know if
you guys have noticed,

02:31.428 --> 02:34.262
but since Brenda and I separated,

02:34.264 --> 02:37.098
I have been doing my own thang.

02:37.100 --> 02:38.466
Oh!

02:38.468 --> 02:40.535
That's why we came to you, Durb Daddy.

02:40.537 --> 02:44.338
Thank you, but... but I was
thinking that a good theme

02:44.340 --> 02:47.059
for the dance would be...

02:48.378 --> 02:50.500
The movie "Congo."

02:50.747 --> 02:52.447
Based on the Michael Crichton novel.

02:52.449 --> 02:53.948
It's got everything teens love.

02:53.950 --> 02:55.883
It's got gorillas, it's got lasers,

02:55.885 --> 02:58.773
it's got a character
named Herkermer Homolka.

03:00.905 --> 03:03.270
Oh. I've seen that look.

03:03.727 --> 03:05.523
Got that look from Brenda for ten years.

03:05.572 --> 03:06.631
She...

03:06.773 --> 03:08.139
She hated all my ideas too.

03:08.141 --> 03:10.699
I'm, it's just...

03:11.883 --> 03:13.161
Mary?

03:13.410 --> 03:15.043
Um, it's just, uh,

03:15.045 --> 03:16.878
obscure movies that no one's seen

03:16.880 --> 03:18.513
- don't make great dance themes.
- Mm-mm.

03:18.515 --> 03:20.882
I'm sorry... You guys have never seen this?

03:20.884 --> 03:23.318
Okay, guys, you gotta
watch this, all right?

03:23.320 --> 03:25.287
And... and if you still
don't think it's a good idea

03:25.289 --> 03:27.322
for a dance, then we won't do it.

03:27.324 --> 03:29.373
- Okay, that's... that's fair.
- Okay.

03:39.036 --> 03:40.437
Okay, all right, all right, listen.

03:40.671 --> 03:42.550
Get in there and rattle him.

03:43.226 --> 03:44.742
Rattle him good.

03:47.912 --> 03:48.962
Mr. Leonard?

03:48.964 --> 03:51.097
Uh, if you want a selfie,
we're gonna have to be quick,

03:51.099 --> 03:53.200
'cause I've got an awful lot
of people out there who...

03:53.202 --> 03:56.376
17 years ago you had sex with
my mom, which makes you my dad.

03:59.808 --> 04:01.242
Huh? Her? Oh.

04:02.841 --> 04:04.794
Theresa Cantrell is your mum?

04:05.144 --> 04:06.743
Theresa the teaser, we used to...

04:06.745 --> 04:08.412
I have a lot of complicated feelings,

04:08.414 --> 04:09.864
and I'm sure you do as well.

04:09.948 --> 04:12.436
I gotta say, I feel, uh, pretty neglected.

04:12.951 --> 04:14.430
A little angry.

04:14.920 --> 04:16.219
Sorry about the timing.

04:16.221 --> 04:17.959
I hope it doesn't mess up your speech.

04:22.132 --> 04:23.204
A son.

04:24.601 --> 04:26.478
Oh, my goodness.

04:26.796 --> 04:29.246
My life just keeps
getting better and better.

04:29.799 --> 04:31.431
All right, let's have a look at you then.

04:31.433 --> 04:32.967
Oh, you're a big lad.

04:33.469 --> 04:34.868
Look at those eyes.

04:34.870 --> 04:36.497
Beautiful... They're mine.

04:36.497 --> 04:38.363
And you've got the forehead.
You've... we've... got...

04:38.365 --> 04:41.633
You've got the same
highly expressive forehead.

04:41.635 --> 04:43.629
- Oh, my goodness me.
- You're on.

04:43.654 --> 04:46.229
Yeah, got it, right. I've
gotta go and do the...

04:47.141 --> 04:48.941
And you wait here, and I'll be back.

04:48.943 --> 04:50.449
Uh...

04:55.716 --> 04:58.880
Hello, Detroit! I have a son!

04:59.053 --> 05:01.146
Yeah!

05:04.792 --> 05:06.282
Well,

05:07.227 --> 05:09.428
Miles was unfazed.

05:09.430 --> 05:12.043
It's like the meaner you
are to him, the nicer he is.

05:12.068 --> 05:14.800
What kind of a dork is thrilled to find out

05:14.802 --> 05:17.202
that he's been saddled
with an unwanted child?

05:20.490 --> 05:22.356
Ah, and that's him calling me right now.

05:22.381 --> 05:23.599
- Yeah? <i>
- Jack.</i>

05:23.624 --> 05:24.807
<i>Hello, old mate.</i>

05:24.807 --> 05:26.173
<i>Do you remember Theresa the teaser?</i>

05:26.174 --> 05:28.074
- Mm-hmm.
<i>- Well, long story short,</i>

05:28.076 --> 05:31.010
<i>she had a baby, and
now I have a son.</i>

05:31.012 --> 05:33.313
<i>And you'll never guess,
he lives in Toledo,</i>

05:33.315 --> 05:34.300
<i>your hometown,</i>

05:34.300 --> 05:36.841
which is where I am right this minute.

05:37.232 --> 05:39.399
Wait, you're in Toledo? Right now?

05:40.357 --> 05:43.552
So we watched the movie "Congo."

05:43.780 --> 05:45.146
And it was good.

05:45.148 --> 05:47.348
- It was very good.
- Very good.

05:47.350 --> 05:49.981
What was your favorite part?
Don't think, just answer.

05:50.520 --> 05:52.953
Easy, when the gorilla
drinks a martini and burps.

05:52.994 --> 05:54.447
Me too!

05:54.492 --> 05:57.610
And while that is all very... funny?

05:57.635 --> 06:00.936
Um, I'm actually starting
to think, just a little bit,

06:01.145 --> 06:03.579
how would you turn that into a dance theme?

06:03.581 --> 06:04.991
As much as I would love to.

06:04.991 --> 06:08.425
Yeah, Durbin, it's like,
What were you even picturing?

06:08.428 --> 06:10.762
How were you even gonna decorate, Ralph?

06:10.764 --> 06:12.497
Take the jungle foliage sets

06:12.499 --> 06:14.543
from last year's production
of "South Pacific"?

06:15.698 --> 06:17.396
Oh, my... Guys, I'm... I'm seeing this.

06:17.397 --> 06:18.950
- This could work.
- Me too.

06:18.975 --> 06:20.156
I can't believe it.

06:20.181 --> 06:22.332
I think we're all actually
coming around to "Congo."

06:22.333 --> 06:24.099
No!

06:24.101 --> 06:25.596
Uh, stop it, Michelle.

06:26.043 --> 06:27.676
Sorry to hurt your feelings, Durbin,

06:27.677 --> 06:28.976
but "Congo" as the dance theme

06:28.978 --> 06:30.594
is the dumbest thing I've ever heard.

06:31.614 --> 06:33.125
It's worse than Fish Week.

06:33.942 --> 06:35.308
Brenda hated Fish Week.

06:35.310 --> 06:38.444
She said it was "unsanitary nonsense."

06:38.446 --> 06:42.270
But, I guess, all my ideas are bad,

06:42.295 --> 06:43.478
aren't they?

06:44.219 --> 06:47.448
You know, you guys, just
do the '80s dance and...

06:47.956 --> 06:49.789
Just do whatever you want.

06:55.530 --> 06:58.164
Guys, this is bad. He
can't know that I live here.

06:58.166 --> 07:00.099
And he can't know that I teach high school.

07:00.101 --> 07:01.367
You can always point out the fact

07:01.369 --> 07:03.069
that you don't teach anything.

07:03.071 --> 07:05.638
What kind of a twisted sicko just shows up

07:05.640 --> 07:07.607
to see his abandoned son?

07:07.609 --> 07:09.083
So pathetic.

07:09.335 --> 07:10.902
Drives all the way here uninvited.

07:10.904 --> 07:13.527
It's like he's so desperate for love.

07:14.289 --> 07:15.708
Yeah, yeah.

07:17.544 --> 07:18.544
You're right.

07:19.212 --> 07:21.145
He's desperate. We can use that.

07:21.466 --> 07:25.340
Okay, so, you need to embrace
your relationship to Miles.

07:25.379 --> 07:27.918
Make him really love you, and then...

07:28.114 --> 07:30.314
Reject him. Hard.

07:30.316 --> 07:32.770
And then we can see if old Miles can float.

07:33.186 --> 07:34.952
Uh, too far, Prince of D.

07:34.954 --> 07:36.621
Why don't we just stick
to the emotional crushing?

07:36.623 --> 07:38.356
I don't know, I feel like the moral compass

07:38.358 --> 07:39.991
is thumbs down on this one.

07:40.140 --> 07:42.136
Yeah, and I feel like I'm pretty
thumbs down on you, Marcus.

07:42.161 --> 07:43.183
Great.

07:43.208 --> 07:46.176
Okay, guys, I need some
ideas for Miles bonding time.

07:46.178 --> 07:48.011
What do you guys like to do
with your parents around here?

07:48.013 --> 07:51.133
You know, the Toledo
Walleye hockey games are fun.

07:51.372 --> 07:53.005
My family has season tickets.

07:53.008 --> 07:54.273
And I'm taking my little brother, Jeffy,

07:54.275 --> 07:55.313
tomorrow night.

07:56.144 --> 07:58.378
My man. Dan, that's perfect.

07:58.380 --> 07:59.941
Okay, so, Devin.

07:59.993 --> 08:02.414
Tomorrow you'll go sightseeing
with Miles after school.

08:02.439 --> 08:05.474
And then, end the evening
at a Walleye hockey game.

08:05.476 --> 08:07.978
Ah, you know how to really
set him up for rejection?

08:09.180 --> 08:10.541
Call him "Dad."

08:11.126 --> 08:13.327
Then it's time for the
pièce de résistance.

08:13.328 --> 08:15.494
Tell him you want nothing to do with him.

08:19.834 --> 08:22.268
Here's to our first Toledo hotdog.

08:22.270 --> 08:23.269
Cheers!

08:25.807 --> 08:27.686
I'm gonna need more of these.

08:28.910 --> 08:32.378
The archduke of Slovenia said,
"Miles, if you'll not take

08:32.380 --> 08:36.198
my daughter, please have
these antique dueling pistols."

08:42.657 --> 08:44.616
Those poachers weren't coming back...

08:44.617 --> 08:45.617
Ow.

08:54.594 --> 08:55.997
Oh, thank you.

08:56.830 --> 08:58.627
Look at us!

08:59.894 --> 09:01.199
Wow.

09:01.482 --> 09:03.181
- That was so good, wasn't it?
- Yeah.

09:03.269 --> 09:05.659
Right, next, onto the game.

09:08.408 --> 09:09.461
Come on.

09:10.176 --> 09:13.967
Let's go, Walleyes.
Let's go, Walleyes.

09:21.585 --> 09:22.952
This is perfect.

09:23.189 --> 09:25.089
Matching father-son hats.

09:25.091 --> 09:27.225
Did you know Miles has a set
of antique dueling pistols?

09:27.227 --> 09:29.060
Don't get sucked into Miles' world, okay?

09:29.062 --> 09:30.428
Stay focused.

09:30.430 --> 09:32.987
Go give him the hats, play the dad card,

09:33.299 --> 09:34.866
break his heart. Go.

09:38.104 --> 09:39.617
Ooh.

09:42.208 --> 09:44.342
Oh, mate, amazing.

09:44.344 --> 09:46.644
A couple of matching fish bubble hats.

09:46.646 --> 09:47.798
Thank you.

09:49.883 --> 09:51.082
Yep.

09:51.084 --> 09:52.983
Oh, one question.

09:54.854 --> 09:56.892
What do I do with these bad boys?

09:57.390 --> 09:58.536
Hey.

09:59.877 --> 10:02.526
Oh, what a couple of willies
in a biscuit, then, eh?

10:04.664 --> 10:06.809
Look, Danny, it's me!

10:09.035 --> 10:11.819
Look at that kid, he's amazing.

10:15.942 --> 10:18.643
Dan, tell Jeffy to stop dancing.

10:18.645 --> 10:20.111
Hey, you tell Jeffy to stop dancing.

10:20.113 --> 10:21.746
Because half these people come to the games

10:21.748 --> 10:23.381
just to see Jeffy dance.

10:25.285 --> 10:27.389
Let's go, Walleyes!

10:31.791 --> 10:34.592
Let's go, Walleyes!

10:34.594 --> 10:36.394
It was truly breathtaking,

10:36.396 --> 10:38.062
but I had no one to share it with.

10:38.064 --> 10:39.505
You climbed Everest?

10:39.766 --> 10:41.564
I've always wanted to do that.

10:41.734 --> 10:43.868
I heard it's covered in frozen corpses.

10:43.870 --> 10:45.125
Well, you can.

10:45.150 --> 10:46.871
Devin, you're... You're a great lad,

10:46.873 --> 10:49.407
and you deserve to see
all the beautiful views

10:49.409 --> 10:52.212
and corpses your... Your
little heart desires.

10:56.749 --> 11:00.101
- Oh, nearly. Nearly.
- _

11:02.755 --> 11:04.355
It kills me to have to do this,

11:04.357 --> 11:06.257
but I've got an early flight
to catch back to Stanford.

11:06.259 --> 11:08.039
Thank you for today. I've had...

11:08.895 --> 11:10.622
an amazing time, and...

11:11.462 --> 11:13.240
I'm never gonna forget today.

11:14.998 --> 11:17.935
Thanks... Dad.

11:20.540 --> 11:21.586
Huh.

11:23.831 --> 11:25.551
Come here, son.

11:31.333 --> 11:32.366
Cheers.

11:32.544 --> 11:35.646
Uh, sorry, guys, can I get
out? Thank you, thank you.

11:35.912 --> 11:37.417
Buh-bye. Cheerio.

11:42.228 --> 11:43.412
Hey, hey!

11:44.130 --> 11:45.597
Why didn't you tell him you hate him?

11:45.599 --> 11:46.731
I'm sorry, Mr. Griffin.

11:46.733 --> 11:48.166
I hesitated and ran out of time.

11:48.168 --> 11:49.601
Can we just get Miles some other way?

11:49.603 --> 11:51.902
No, there is no other way. This is the way.

11:53.603 --> 11:54.672
All right, come on, let's go.

11:54.674 --> 11:56.975
Not yet. I don't wanna wake Jeffy.

11:56.977 --> 11:58.676
I literally have to do everything.

11:58.678 --> 11:59.911
All right, fine, give me Jeffy.

11:59.913 --> 12:01.446
Come on. All right, Jeffy, let's go.

12:01.448 --> 12:03.014
Come on, Jeffy.

12:03.016 --> 12:03.982
Okay.

12:03.984 --> 12:05.326
All right.

12:05.552 --> 12:07.752
I'll figure out how to keep
Miles in Toledo another day.

12:07.754 --> 12:09.354
You figure out how to
grow some balls, all right?

12:09.356 --> 12:10.443
Finish him!

12:10.590 --> 12:12.257
Ah, okay, shh.

12:12.259 --> 12:13.781
It's all right. Come here, Jeffy.

12:21.043 --> 12:23.432
- Hello, Jack-o!
- Miles-o.

12:23.739 --> 12:25.306
Uh, how'd it go with your son?

12:25.308 --> 12:27.441
It must've felt nice to
say sorry for having missed

12:27.443 --> 12:30.110
every significant event in his entire life,

12:30.112 --> 12:33.080
<i>you know, baseball
games, recitals...</i>

12:33.082 --> 12:34.961
Aw, his wobbly first step.

12:36.185 --> 12:38.702
Well, I... I didn't exactly get a chance to

12:39.525 --> 12:40.854
tell him all those things.

12:40.856 --> 12:42.423
Ah, that's a shame.

12:42.425 --> 12:44.592
I would've killed to
hear my absentee father

12:44.594 --> 12:46.393
<i>say sorry to me for
missing all that stuff</i>

12:46.395 --> 12:48.128
<i>in my life, you know, in person.</i>

12:48.128 --> 12:49.380
My two cents?

12:49.731 --> 12:52.003
I think it's worth, uh,
sticking around one more day

12:52.028 --> 12:53.076
to tell him all that.

12:53.101 --> 12:56.736
You know Jack, that is
smarter than a seaman's cleats.

12:56.738 --> 12:58.471
That can't be an actual British expression.

12:58.759 --> 13:00.744
All right, cheerio, me old China.

13:01.376 --> 13:04.544
- Uh-oh.
- D-D-Durbie Fully Loaded.

13:04.944 --> 13:07.111
Let me guess, you guys are here to tell me

13:07.113 --> 13:08.912
that eating salty soup out of a cup

13:08.914 --> 13:10.948
is another one of my bad ideas?

13:10.950 --> 13:12.616
No, Durbs, we're actually here to tell you

13:12.618 --> 13:14.513
that we are totally on board for "Congo."

13:15.020 --> 13:17.801
Like you said before, it's a bad idea.

13:17.826 --> 13:20.126
We were talking about it and
realized we're the only ones

13:20.166 --> 13:21.626
who care about the dance theme.

13:21.651 --> 13:22.627
Yeah.

13:22.627 --> 13:24.260
The kids don't pay
attention to the decorations.

13:24.262 --> 13:25.753
They just see them as
something to hide behind

13:25.778 --> 13:27.110
so they can grab up on a butt.

13:27.135 --> 13:28.935
Mm-hmm, yeah, it makes no difference

13:28.937 --> 13:30.904
whether they're honking on
each other's little [BLEEP]

13:30.906 --> 13:34.474
behind a jungle in the Congo,
or a big '80s Rubik's Cube.

13:34.476 --> 13:35.876
I mean, it's true.

13:35.878 --> 13:38.018
The... these dances
are a full-on dog park.

13:38.018 --> 13:39.184
In every way.

13:39.185 --> 13:40.930
I found two poops last year.

13:41.087 --> 13:42.363
Human.

13:42.455 --> 13:44.685
Ralph, we just wanna support you.

13:44.924 --> 13:47.635
I mean, that means so much
more to us than some theme.

13:47.894 --> 13:50.157
You guys are the best.

13:51.015 --> 13:52.015
Listen.

13:52.645 --> 13:55.179
Keep this under your hats, okay?

13:55.181 --> 13:57.481
We don't want some other
school stealing our theme.

13:57.483 --> 13:59.685
We are literally, um, never

13:59.710 --> 14:01.835
telling anyone about this.

14:02.262 --> 14:04.082
Ever. Okay?

14:17.694 --> 14:19.467
Uh, sorry to interrupt.

14:21.962 --> 14:24.844
Is this... is this Biology class?

14:25.566 --> 14:27.832
Ah, hah, there he is.

14:28.142 --> 14:29.642
Miles, what're you doing here?

14:29.644 --> 14:33.279
Well, I... I realized that
I never apologized to you,

14:33.281 --> 14:35.294
